OL,3,CNo evidence of police collusion in
OL,4,C1978 La Mon bombing, says ombudsman
OL,6,FThe Police Ombudsman said that despite
OL,7,Fconcerns that informants may have been
OL,8,Finvolved in the bombing, "collusive
OL,9,Fbehaviours" were not a feature of the
OL,10,FRoyal Ulster Constabulary (RUC)
OL,11,Finvestigation.
OL,13,FSenior director of investigations with
OL,14,Fthe Police Ombudsman's Office, Paul
OL,15,FHolmes, said investigators did not
OL,16,Ffind evidence or intelligence that
OL,17,Fwould support the suggestion of
OL,18,Fmalpractice by police officers and
OL,19,Ffound no intelligence which could have
OL,20,Fforewarned of, or prevented, the
OL,21,Fbombing.
